      "writtenOn": "2020-06-27T07:44:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i think we shouldn\u0027t use it in Fetch(), but in run(). let\u0027s step back.\n\nthe reason mask.Mask has Trim() is because it was designed for datastore where the client must read entire row. In Spanner, we can choose columns to read, so instead we should dynamically generate the list of columns below.\n\nif we don\u0027t do that, then we\u0027d be reading large summary HTML from Spanner, and then throwing it away",
